## S hareho l der voting

As required by King IV and the JSE Listings Requirements, Vodacom will put a dual advisory vote to shareholders regarding the approval of the remuneration policy and the implementation thereof. Should either vote receive 25% or more votes against it, Vodacom will take the following steps:

- glyph<c=3,font=/AACDCN+Wingdings-Regular> z Issue a Stock Exchange News Service (SENS) announcement regarding the voting results;
- glyph<c=3,font=/AACDCN+Wingdings-Regular> z Invite shareholders to engage with Vodacom regarding their dissatisfaction with either vote;
- glyph<c=3,font=/AACDCN+Wingdings-Regular> z Schedule collective and/or individual engagements with relevant shareholders to record their concerns and objections;
- glyph<c=3,font=/AACDCN+Wingdings-Regular> z Assimilate all responses and schedule a RemCo session to analyse concerns and issues raised to formulate changes to policy and implementation where required; and
- glyph<c=3,font=/AACDCN+Wingdings-Regular> z Develop a formal response to shareholders who articulates concerns raised and changes to be made to address them, and detail responses to concerns where Vodacom, despite shareholder feedback, believes its current policy and/or implementation is adequate.

